The paper deals with the problem of computing low-weight spanning trees with degree constraints, which is a fundamental problem in computational geometry and graph theory. The paper presents results for points in the plane and in higher dimensions, which suggests that it could belong to categories such as cs.DS (data structures and algorithms), cs.CG (computational geometry), and cs.NA (numerical analysis). The paper also involves optimization and approximation techniques, which could place it in categories such as cs.GT (game theory) and cs.DM (discrete mathematics).
